name: Blazing /lʌɪn/
description: If the glare of the public eye becomes too much for us, our inner child may assert its rights, and our bodily shadow may transform into our mental second self, becoming our anchor, keeping us grounded, and providing us with depth and intensity. We gain rootedness, insight, and new worldly wisdom by retreating from the blaze of display into our substantial self. by @Baimtje
